Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Beat butter and 1/4 cup SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add flour beating at low speed until blended. Stir in vanilla and pecans. Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake 20 minutes; remove from oven and place on wire racks to cool. Process 2 tablespoons SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener and cornstarch in a blender or food processor; roll cookies in powdered SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener mixture.